\begin_layout Standard
When a data type is a semigroup, it is often possible to find a special
 value that acts as an 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

empty
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 value with respect to the semigroup operation.
 Combining the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

empty
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 value with another value will not change that value.
 For instance, concatenating with an empty list does not change a given
 list; so, the empty list is the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

empty
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 value for lists.
 Adding zero to an integer does not change that integer; so, zero is the
 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

empty
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 value when adding integers.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A semigroup with a designated 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

empty
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 value is called a 
\series bold
monoid
\series default

\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
