 The identity law holds because:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
 & \quad\text{expect to equal }(b^{:B}\rightarrow\bbnum 0+b)^{\uparrow F}:\quad\\
 & p^{\bbnum 0,B}=\,\begin{array}{|c||c|}
 & F^{\bbnum 0+B}\\
